Study

Cluster Autoscaler: scales node groups based on unschedulable pods. ASG-based.
Karpenter: provisions nodes directly via EC2 API, picks instance types just-in-time. Faster, more flexible.
EKS upgrades: control plane → node groups → addons (CoreDNS, kube-proxy, VPC CNI).
Hands-On

# Deploy app + ALB ingress to EKS
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f service.yaml
kubectl apply -f ingress.yaml   # annotated for ALB

# Install Karpenter (per docs), define a NodePool/EC2NodeClass
# Scale a deployment to force node provisioning
kubectl scale deploy web --replicas=50
kubectl get nodes -w

